Project description

Kiwi is an efficient C++ implementation of the Cassowary constraint solvingalgorithm. Kiwi is an implementation of the algorithm based on theseminal Cassowary paper.It is not a refactoring of the original C++ solver. Kiwi has been designedfrom the ground up to be lightweight and fast. Kiwi ranges from 10x to 500xfaster than the original Cassowary solver with typical use cases gaining a 40ximprovement. Memory savings are consistently > 5x.

In addition to the C++ solver, Kiwi ships with hand-rolled Python bindings forPython 3.7+.
